	     ON November 22, the Ibisi SAPS Crime Prevention Unit received information about alleged drug dealers­ in the Ethembeni area in Ibisi and two homes were subsequently raided. Two suspects, aged 23 and 29, were arrested.  Police were told that drugs are being made available to pupils. When police arrived at the alleged drug dealers homes they seized dagga with an estimated street value of R5 000, and R640 in cash.  The suspects were charged for being in possession of unlawful drugs.  On November 23 the 23 year old was released on R800 bail and the other suspect paid a R200 fine. The case was remanded to January 9, 2018. - Supplied  24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  